  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "Unfortunately, Facebook Chat (including Messenger) **no longer supports using underscores (_) for underlining or asterisks (*) for bolding.**  They removed this functionality a while ago.\n\n**Here's what you *can* do to emphasize text in Facebook Chat:**\n\n*   **Emojis:** Use emojis to highlight certain words or add emphasis. For example, \ud83d\udd25 for \"hot\" or \ud83d\udcaf for \"great.\"\n*   **Capitalization:** Using ALL CAPS is a classic way to show emphasis, but be careful, as it can come across as shouting. Use it sparingly.\n*   **Spacing:** You can strategically use extra spacing (like blank lines) to separate and highlight a particular sentence or phrase.\n*   **Word Choice:** Choose stronger verbs or adjectives to make your point more effectively. For example, instead of \"I like it,\" say \"I *love* it!\" or \"It's *amazing*!\"\n*   **External Tools (limited):** There are some third-party websites or apps that *claim* to format text that you can then copy and paste into Facebook Chat. However:\n    *   **Be very cautious.** Many of these are unreliable or contain malware.  Only use trusted sources.\n    *   **The formatting might not always translate perfectly** and could appear differently or not at all on the recipient's end.\n    *   **Facebook could change their code at any time**, rendering these workarounds ineffective.\n\n**The Bottom Line:** Facebook has intentionally limited text formatting options in chat. Emphasize your message using the techniques above instead of relying on unsupported formatting.",
